article.description: Van leads Montana past Cent Washington 48-14
article.headline: Van leads Montana past Cent Washington 48-14
article.linkText: Van leads Montana past Cent Washington 48-14
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. -- Travon Van scored four touchdowns Saturday to propel Montana to a 48-14 victory over Central Washington. Montana, playing without injured starting quarterback Jordan Johnson, moved to 1-1 on the season in handing the Division II Wildcats a loss in their first game of the year. Van scored the first three times he touched the ball -- on runs of 31 and 9 yards and an 85-yard pass from Shay Smithwick-Hann to lead the Grizzlies to a 34-7 halftime lead. Van added a fourth touchdown in the third quarter on a 43-yard run. Tucker Schye picked up a fumbled punt by teammate John Nguyen and returned it 46 yards for a touchdown and Harrison Greenberg booted a 29-yard field goal to round out Montana's first-half scoring. Central Washington got on the scoreboard with 10:06 to play in the half on a 13-yard pass from Jake Nelson to Kent McKinney Jr.
